[size=4][b]Note[/b][/size]

[size=3]Mod is disabled until you have completed the intro set of quests (where you come back from the village and give Gerry a beer).[/size]

[size=4][b]Very Important[/b][/size]

[size=3]Back up your saves before playing with the config. Everything tested fine on my machine, but better to be safe than sorry.[/size]

[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3][b]Saving[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Save anytime[/b] by pressing K (rebindable), or with a controller button if you prefer. The controller button won't trigger while any menu is open, so it can share a binding with menu navigation (for example, LT also switches pages in the tech tree).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-save on a timer[/b] — 1 to 60 minute slider, default 10 minutes.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Save on new day[/b] — independent of the auto-save timer.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Save on exit[/b] — choose to save before going back to the main menu or desktop.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]New file or overwrite[/b] — for each save type (manual / auto / new day) pick whether it creates a fresh file or overwrites the currently loaded one.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Save-and-exit straight to desktop[/b] — skip the main menu if you'd rather go straight back to Windows.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Backup every save[/b] to a separate folder as an extra safety net against save corruption.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Loading[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Restores your exact position[/b] on reload — even after exiting to desktop. Vanilla drops you at a fixed spawn.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Tidier load-game list[/b] — pick Real Time or Game Time sort, pick Descending or Ascending direction, show up to 100 saves (or unlimited).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Pin Last Played To Top[/b] — keeps the save you most recently loaded or saved at the top of the list regardless of sort order.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Controller focus on latest save[/b] — opening the load menu with a controller jumps focus to your most recent save instead of landing on the New Game button.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Other[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Main menu update notice[/b] — flags when a newer version of this mod (or other mods in my collection) is available on Nexus. Click an entry to open its Nexus page. Opt-out via "Check for Updates".[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — one shared inventory across all workstations. Complements Save Now if you've been avoiding the save-scum-and-reload cycle to get around vanilla's inventory split.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/53]Longer Days[/url] — stretches the day cycle so you can fit more into a single "day-length" auto-save window.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/42]Exhaust-less[/url] — halves costs on energy, gratitude, and sanity so marathon sessions between saves hurt less.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

